OL,3,CBristol celebrates scaled-down St
OL,4,CPauls Carnival after spiralling costs
OL,6,FExecutive director LaToyah McAllister-
OL,7,FJones said she is still optimistic the
OL,8,Fevent will be a key part of Bristol's
OL,9,Fcalendar.
OL,11,FShe said: "It's so important for our
OL,12,Fcultural heritage, our city and our
OL,13,Felders. I don't think you can take
OL,14,Fcarnival out of Bristol and Bristol
OL,15,Fstill be Bristol. While it's harsh out
OL,16,Fthere we are going to find a ways of
OL,17,Fsolving that."
